{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"What happens when water moves too slowly to notice? In Everglades National Park, it shapes everything. Covering around 6,100 square kilometres, the park was established in 1947 to protect a wetland system unlike any other in the United States. As a recognised UNESCO World Heritage Site, the park's elevated pinelands rise above the marshes and prairies that form one of the world's largest wetland systems.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SlashPine_ROW9169451135_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SlashPine_ROW9169451135_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Forest hammock of slash pine and saw palmetto, Everglades National Park, Florida, United States","Copyright":"© Mary Liz Austin/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260424_SlashPine\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Everglades+National+Park+Florida&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260424_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260424_SlashPine"},"Ssd":"20260424","Name":"SlashPine","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9169451135","FullDateString":"24 апр. 2026 г."},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Small, lively and instantly recognisable by its call: the chiffchaff is one of Germany's most common songbirds and a true harbinger of spring. As early as late February, the first males return from their winter quarters in the Mediterranean or south-western Europe and begin their distinctive song, which gives the species its name. This clear 'chiff-chaff, chiff-chaff' makes it easy to locate, even when it remains hidden in dense vegetation.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ChiffchaffSpring_ROW0928406195_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ChiffchaffSpring_ROW0928406195_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Common chiffchaff, Germany","Copyright":"© Andyworks/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260423_ChiffchaffSpring\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Common+chiffchaff&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260423_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260423_ChiffchaffSpring"},"Ssd":"20260423","Name":"ChiffchaffSpring","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0928406195","FullDateString":"23 апр. 2026 г."},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Take Alam-Pedja Nature Reserve in Estonia—what makes it so special? Established in 1994, it protects one of the country's largest and most intact wetland systems, where rivers like the Pedja and Põltsamaa still flow freely. The 342-square-kilometres reserve is a haven for wildlife. Moose roam the wetlands, lynx move through dense forests and rare birds such as the black stork and lesser spotted eagle nest in its quieter corners. With limited human settlement, much of the area remains untouched—no large-scale farming, no urban spread. Seasonal flooding reshapes the landscape, renewing habitats and sustaining rich biodiversity year after year.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.TartuEstonia_ROW8518008837_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.TartuEstonia_ROW8518008837_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Alam-Pedja Nature Reserve in Tartu County, Estonia","Copyright":"© Sven Zacek/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260422_TartuEstonia\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Alam+Pedja+Nature+Reserve&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260422_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260422_TartuEstonia"},"Ssd":"20260422","Name":"TartuEstonia","Market":"ROW","Hash":"8518008837","FullDateString":"22 апр. 2026 г."},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Spring arrives with a small, spiky ambassador: the European hedgehog, spotted here in France. Part cuddle, part survival gear, this tiny forager is mostly nocturnal and usually solitary, guided mainly by smell and sound. Its job description is simple: roam, sniff through leaf litter and vacuum up invertebrates like worms, beetles, slugs and caterpillars—the kind of snacks that keep ecosystems running and gardeners smiling. When danger shows up, it doesn't negotiate or flee. It curls into a tight ball and lets its spines do the talking.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SpringHedgehog_ROW8347906365_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SpringHedgehog_ROW8347906365_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"European hedgehog, France","Copyright":"© Klein & Hubert/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260421_SpringHedgehog\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=European+hedgehog&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260421_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260421_SpringHedgehog"},"Ssd":"20260421","Name":"SpringHedgehog","Market":"ROW","Hash":"8347906365","FullDateString":"21 апр. 2026 г."},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"In south-eastern Utah, USA, Canyonlands National Park reveals a vast, rugged landscape shaped over millions of years by the Colorado and Green rivers. Established in 1964, the park protects a maze of canyons, mesas and buttes carved into layers of ancient rock. Divided into districts such as Island in the Sky and The Needles, it offers sweeping views that shift with the light from dawn to dusk.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SunsetKiva_ROW8130256678_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SunsetKiva_ROW8130256678_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Sunset in Canyonlands National Park, Moab, Utah, United States","Copyright":"© Jason Hatfield/Tandem Stills + Motion","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260420_SunsetKiva\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Canyonlands+National+Park+Moab&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260420_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260420_SunsetKiva"},"Ssd":"20260420","Name":"SunsetKiva","Market":"ROW","Hash":"8130256678","FullDateString":"20 апр. 2026 г."},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"From above, Brazil's Mirror Beach looks like a watercolour you can walk into. Pale cliffs, reefs stitched into the shoreline and a mosaic of tide pools that, at low tide, reflect the sky and clouds so clearly that the beach earns its name. Tucked into Bahia, a north-eastern state on the Atlantic coast, it sits between small fishing villages in the city of Porto Seguro. Access follows dirt roads and short trails—a natural crowd-control system that keeps the vibe intimate. For years, it stayed off the map, known only through word of mouth, until the 1990s brought it onto travellers' radars.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.TranBA_ROW7860007942_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.TranBA_ROW7860007942_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Mirror Beach, Porto Seguro, Bahia, Brazil","Copyright":"© Marcelo Nacinovic/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260419_TranBA\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Bahia+Brazil&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260419_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260419_TranBA"},"Ssd":"20260419","Name":"TranBA","Market":"ROW","Hash":"7860007942","FullDateString":"19 апр. 2026 г."},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Rolling hills in Tuscany, Italy, feel like they've been styled with intent—soft curves, neat rows of vines and those tall, unmistakable cypress trees. Have you ever noticed how the landscape seems to change colour with the seasons? Spring brings bright greens and wildflowers, summer turns fields golden and autumn deepens everything into warm, earthy tones.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ToscanaSpring_ROW0859656735_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ToscanaSpring_ROW0859656735_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Rolling hills of Tuscany, Italy","Copyright":"© Andyworks/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260418_ToscanaSpring\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Tuscany+Italy&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260418_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260418_ToscanaSpring"},"Ssd":"20260418","Name":"ToscanaSpring","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0859656735","FullDateString":"18 апр. 2026 г."}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"At the far edge of Ynys Llanddwyn, where the land quietly gives way to sea, Tŵr Mawr Lighthouse stands watch without making a fuss. It is not tall, not flashy, but it knows its purpose—and it keeps it bright.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.TwrMawrLighthouse2026_ROW9390350989_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.TwrMawrLighthouse2026_ROW9390350989_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Tŵr Mawr lighthouse on Llanddwyn Island in Anglesey, Wales","Copyright":"© Lukas Bischoff/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260501_TwrMawrLighthouse2026\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Twr+Mawr+Lighthouse&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260501_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260501_TwrMawrLighthouse2026"},"Ssd":"20260501","Name":"TwrMawrLighthouse2026","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9390350989","FullDateString":"1 мая 2026 г."},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Imagine a flower sparking a financial frenzy. Sounds unlikely, right? Yet in the 1630s, tulips did exactly that in the Netherlands. During tulip mania, rare bulbs became luxury items traded for astonishing sums—some valued at prices comparable to a house. Why so valuable? Unusual colours and striped patterns were scarce and unpredictable, and collectors wanted the rarest varieties they could find.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.DutchTulips_ROW0532367282_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.DutchTulips_ROW0532367282_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Grape hyacinths and tulips, Keukenhof Gardens, Lisse, Netherlands","Copyright":"© Martin Ruegner/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260430_DutchTulips\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Keukenhof+Gardens&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260430_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260430_DutchTulips"},"Ssd":"20260430","Name":"DutchTulips","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0532367282","FullDateString":"30 апр. 2026 г."},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Ships leaving Lisbon once passed a small stone tower before meeting the wide Atlantic. That tower, standing on the bank of the Tagus River, served as both a guardian and a farewell. Say hello to Belém Tower—a fortress that watched Portugal sail into the Age of Exploration.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BelemTowerBank_ROW0291299958_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BelemTowerBank_ROW0291299958_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Belém Tower on the bank of the Tagus River, Lisbon, Portugal","Copyright":"© f9photos/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260429_BelemTowerBank\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Belem+Tower&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260429_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260429_BelemTowerBank"},"Ssd":"20260429","Name":"BelemTowerBank","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0291299958","FullDateString":"29 апр. 2026 г."},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"The spectacled bear, also known as the Andean bear, is the only South American bear of the Ursidae family. Inhabiting the northern and central Andes Mountains, it dwells primarily in forested areas and feeds mainly on shoots and fruit. Pale markings around the eyes often resemble eyeglasses, or 'spectacles,' giving the species its distinctive name.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.AndeanBear_ROW0128606931_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.AndeanBear_ROW0128606931_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Spectacled bear resting in tree, Ecuador","Copyright":"© Andy Rouse/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260428_AndeanBear\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Spectacled+bear&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260428_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260428_AndeanBear"},"Ssd":"20260428","Name":"AndeanBear","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0128606931","FullDateString":"28 апр. 2026 г."},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Designed by architect Giuseppe Mengoni and completed in 1877, the Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II in Milan, Italy, is one of the world's oldest and most famous shopping arcades. Located between Piazza del Duomo and Piazza della Scala, it features a stunning glass-and-iron roof and an elegant, octagonal layout. Affectionately known as 'Milan's living room,' the Galleria is home to high-end boutiques, historic cafés such as Caffè Biffi and Camparino in Galleria, and renowned restaurants.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MilanGalleria_ROW9826130780_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MilanGalleria_ROW9826130780_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"The glass dome of Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II, Milan, Italy","Copyright":"© PhillipMinnis/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260427_MilanGalleria\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Galleria+Vittorio+Emanuele+II+Milan+Italy&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260427_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260427_MilanGalleria"},"Ssd":"20260427","Name":"MilanGalleria","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9826130780","FullDateString":"27 апр. 2026 г."},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Spring brings apple trees to life with clouds of soft pink blossoms. Their delicate petals brighten orchards and hillsides, standing out against clear blue skies as the season shifts from winter toward warmer days. These blooms attract pollinators such as bees and butterflies, helping fruit trees produce the apples that will grow later in the year.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.AppleBlossoms_ROW9623403964_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.AppleBlossoms_ROW9623403964_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Pink apple blossoms, Avila Beach, California, United States","Copyright":"© Mimi Ditchie Photography/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260426_AppleBlossoms\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Apple+tree&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260426_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260426_AppleBlossoms"},"Ssd":"20260426","Name":"AppleBlossoms","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9623403964","FullDateString":"26 апр. 2026 г."},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Penguins usually bring Antarctica to mind, but these endearing flightless seabirds don't always follow the ice. Found only in the Galápagos Islands—a volcanic archipelago about 966 kilometres off Ecuador's coast—the Galápagos penguins pictured here live farther north than any other penguin. Cool, nutrient‑rich ocean currents make this equatorial habitat possible by supplying food and keeping surrounding waters within survivable temperatures. Compact and agile, these birds spend much of the day in the water to stay cool.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.GalapagosPenguins_ROW9365376155_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.GalapagosPenguins_ROW9365376155_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Galápagos penguins swimming, Galápagos Islands, Ecuador","Copyright":"© Henley Spiers/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260425_GalapagosPenguins\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Galapagos+penguins&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260425_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId"